1
00:00:00,916 --> 00:00:02,750
AWS HealthLake Overview

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,916
AWS HealthLake is a HIPAA-eligible
service

3
00:00:08,124 --> 00:00:10,666
that health care and life sciences
companies 

4
00:00:10,683 --> 00:00:13,500
can use to store, transform, query

5
00:00:13,583 --> 00:00:15,750
and analyze large-scale health data

6
00:00:15,833 --> 00:00:17,500
following FHIR standard.

7
00:00:17,916 --> 00:00:21,416
FHIR stands for Fast Healthcare
Interoperability Resource.

8
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:24,083
You can use HealthLake

9
00:00:24,083 --> 00:00:26,833
to organize, index, and structure

10
00:00:26,916 --> 00:00:28,708
patient information in a way

11
00:00:28,766 --> 00:00:31,866
that is secure, compliant, and can be
audited.

12
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:35,416
HealthLake uses machine learning models

13
00:00:35,416 --> 00:00:37,166
to automatically understand

14
00:00:37,166 --> 00:00:39,666
and extract meaningful medical
information

15
00:00:39,708 --> 00:00:40,958
from the raw data.

16
00:00:43,291 --> 00:00:45,291
AWS HealthLake use cases.

17
00:00:45,833 --> 00:00:47,583
Manage population health.

18
00:00:48,041 --> 00:00:50,666
HealthLake helps healthcare organizations

19
00:00:50,708 --> 00:00:53,708
analyze population health trends, costs,

20
00:00:54,041 --> 00:00:56,416
and choose better care management options.

21
00:00:57,291 --> 00:00:58,875
Improve quality of care.

22
00:00:59,541 --> 00:01:02,125
Hospitals, health insurance companies

23
00:01:02,125 --> 00:01:04,416
and life sciences organizations

24
00:01:04,458 --> 00:01:05,625
use HealthLake

25
00:01:05,666 --> 00:01:07,375
to improve quality of care

26
00:01:07,375 --> 00:01:08,708
and reduce cost

27
00:01:08,833 --> 00:01:11,916
by compiling a complete view of a
patient's medical history.

28
00:01:12,916 --> 00:01:14,875
Optimize hospital efficiency.

29
00:01:15,458 --> 00:01:17,416
HealthLake offers hospitals

30
00:01:17,458 --> 00:01:19,625
analytics and machine learning tools

31
00:01:19,666 --> 00:01:22,500
to improve efficiency and reduce hospital
waste.

32
00:01:24,541 --> 00:01:26,458
AWS HealthLake benefits.

33
00:01:27,375 --> 00:01:29,125
Quickly ingest health data.

34
00:01:29,750 --> 00:01:32,041
Using the HealthLake Import API.

35
00:01:32,166 --> 00:01:35,166
you can migrate FHIR files from Amazon S3

36
00:01:35,225 --> 00:01:36,875
to your HealthLake datastore

37
00:01:37,041 --> 00:01:41,750
including clinical notes, lab reports,
insurance claims, and more.

38
00:01:42,791 --> 00:01:44,541
Store health data securely.

39
00:01:45,291 --> 00:01:47,708
AWS HealthLake creates a datastore

40
00:01:47,708 --> 00:01:50,625
that stores health records in a
FHIR-compliant format.

41
00:01:51,083 --> 00:01:53,083
The datastore creates a complete view

42
00:01:53,333 --> 00:01:56,500
of each patient's medical history in
chronological order.

43
00:01:57,291 --> 00:02:01,125
AWS HealthLake supports multiple
security and access controls

44
00:02:01,125 --> 00:02:03,500
to ensure patient-sensitive health data

45
00:02:03,500 --> 00:02:06,291
is protected and meets regulatory
compliance.

46
00:02:07,291 --> 00:02:09,541
Transform unstructured medical data.

47
00:02:10,124 --> 00:02:16,791
HealthLake provides integrated medical
natural language processing, NLP, using Amazon Comprehend Medical.

48
00:02:17,541 --> 00:02:21,708
Raw medical text data is transformed using
specialized ML models.

49
00:02:22,541 --> 00:02:28,291
These models have been trained to
understand and extract meaningful information from unstructured healthcare data.

50
00:02:30,541 --> 00:02:34,541
This is the end of Amazon HealthLake
overview. Thanks for watching.

